articles.title: Do YOU have 'tokophobia'? Study suggests 62% of women suffer from little-known condition - Daily Mail
articles.description: A study published last month found that 62 percent of American women have tokophobia, or the fear of childbirth. This fear was most pronounced in black and disadvantaged women.
articles.content:
The condition 'tokophobia' probably means nothing to you, but doctors warn that there's a high chance you have it.

articles.title: Texas sends ban on gender-affirming care for minors to governor's desk - CNN
articles.description: The Texas legislature Wednesday night voted to ban gender-affirming care for most minors, sending a bill to the governor’s desk that, if enacted, would put critical health care out of reach for transgender youth in America’s second-most-populous state.
